</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: yeah...</span><hr size=1> The Draper incident was not the start of the bad blood between the 2 teams. In game 3(I think) of that same series back in 96 one of the russians thugs on Detroit (Konstantinov maybe) checked Adam Foote away from the play and grabbed the back of his head, and rammed it into the glass. Foote got up with blood pouring down his face looking for a ref to call a penalty (easily a double minor). Since it was away from the play, the ref's didn't see it and didn't call a penalty. I'm pretty sure it was in Denver, which means it had to be game 3 or 4 (Detroit had home ice that year). Yes, you are so right to praise Konstantinov (if that's who I'm thinking of that did this). That's pure class to ram a guys head into the glass with your hand when you know the refs aren't looking.<br>
<br>
The Draper incident was in game 6 of that series I believe. Yes Lemieux's hit was cheap, but Draper was a dumbass to have his head down next to the boards when he had the puck anyway. He was asking to get hit. Anyway neither Lemieux or Konstantinov are playing for those teams anymore. Konstantinov is the one that got paralyzed in a limo wreck, right? I don't remember who Lemieux plays for now, but I think he's still playing for some eastern conference team (not New Jersey).<br>
<br>
Now, you say the entire Av's team is cowards because of one players actions? Even though that player has not played for Colorado in at least 3 years? Get over it. Players like Joe Sakic, Peter Forsberg, Chris Drury, Milan Hejduk, Rob Blake and Adam Foote are pure class. Both teams have outstanding players and most of them are classy guys. I respect Yzerman, Shanahan, Hasek, Larionov and I don't hold Konstantinov's cheap shot on Foote against the entire team.  One players bad decision should not reflect the entire teams reputation, especially if he doesn't even play for that team anymore. Move on. <p><B><I><FONT FACE="verdana"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="880020">Ji<FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="770560">ng</FONT><BR>60 Or<FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="770560">ac</FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="700980">le </FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="661290">of</FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="6115a0"> Dr</FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="5519c1">in</FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="4824d8">al</FONT></FONT><BR></B></I><BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ukaria5.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karia5</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>League of Legends Princess</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/1/02 7:36:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=820.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: yeah...</span><hr size=1> As a fan of hockey, I don't like to see hits like the ones delivered on Foote or Draper in the 96 series.  Nevertheless, if you want to call a team cowards, for a few players actions, I'd be looking at the Red Wings.  They are pretty much renowned throughout the NHL for their cheap shots.       <p> <center> <image src = "http://home.attbi.com/~renw111/wsb/media/12544/graphic.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uboofy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Boofy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><HR><font color=#660066><CENTER>Drinal Ally<BR>******</CENTER></font><HR></span><br>  Posts: 819<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/1/02 8:22:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=820.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ....</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry, but Chelleos's (SP) cheapness is only matched by Nolen's (San Jose) bitchyness....  Did you watch the Sharks/Avs series?  Whine whine bitch bitch on every ref call....  And same goes to Chelleos...  Both those guys are pussies.<br>
<br>
As for the rest of the players?  Forsberg, commin right into the playoffs after a season injured.....that boy has talent.  Heydue, or heidue, or whatever....  Had the most shots for the avs in the wings series...not one goal...  Boy needs some practice...  Drury.... scores when we need it...good for OT...but shit, not for anything else...  Adam Foote.... STAY out of the penalty box...  As for the Wings...  They aren't to bad...  42 saves a game doesn't mean that Roy is an awesome goalie....  it means Avs defense blows.<br>
<br>
But anyway...it's all over now....  Maybe next year....<br>
<br>
-Boof <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ujahooty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jahooty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Lubba</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/2/02 9:38:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=820.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ....</span><hr size=1> Hey Jing<br>
<br>
<br>
You show your intelligence lvl....<br>
<br>
He was a dumb ass for having his head down? <br>
<br>
That condones having your jaw broke? We arent talking a bloody nose here, we are talking he got mulched. Not even close to the same thing.<br>
<br>
Did a single person ever say..we are sorry he did that to Draper? I sure dont remember ever reading it. I know if I did something to a person that inflicted that type of damage, I would have been the first in line to say I was sorry it happened.<br>
<br>
O well..I guess there are 2 sides to every story.<br>
<br>
If ONE person from that org would have stepped up, then I wouldnt have a problem with the Avs. Matter of fact I would respect em as a winning type franchise. They have a few players I am sure will make the hall someday and Joy Boy Roy is arguably the best of all time.  But they didnt step up. I am sure the Broncos would have apologized for doing something like this. The Romo spitting in the face incident had an apology and no physical damage was done. Colorado has one team I respect...Nuff said<br>
<br>
Bottom line..<br>
Your team got their arse spanked..the better team won. <br>
As soon as the blisters subside, they can have a celebration for being runner up in the conference. Damn that shut out must have hurt.<br>
<br>
Hooty<br>
