And my Devils sucked this year. <p><img src="http://www.skybyrd.net/soulbonded/oakersiggy.gif" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ujahooty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jahooty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Lubba</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/3/02 10:00:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=820.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ....</span><hr size=1> Yeah Jing<br>
<br>
You said it was a cheap shot...but you also brought up the bloody nose which was an attempt at saying..Detroit started it by doing this bad thing.<br>
<br>
Palming others faces, spraying the goalies face with ice when he is down, etc..it is all part of hockey. Getting minor injuries is probably what makes the game so exciting to a lot of fans.<br>
<br>
But the serious stuff makes ya stick your head up and say WTF.<br>
I think it was Dale Hunter that gave that check during the playoffs a few yrs ago after a goal was scored. Dislocated/seperated the players shoulder. He received a 21 game suspension the next yr.<br>
<br>
If a Vladdy or ruff type player had been the one hit, then  an arguement could of been made for what happened. But it was a little guy that plays clean hockey who got railed.If Sakic(or even a much less talented but clean playing Av) had been the one with his face mangled, you would understand where I am coming from.<br>
<br>
In EQ terms it would be training a low lvl grp and giving em a TPW then saying...they shouldnt have been there. They hadnt ever been guilty of KSing ya or anything, but just happened to be in the wrong place. No legitimate justification to say... Serves em right... rather than..I am sorry and can I help ya in any way.<br>
<br>
O well..you have your views and I have mine...just as you have your team you enjoy. I just dont happen to think very highly of the Avs franchise. You on the other hand owe the Avs 2 cups to Det. If we didnt have the ability to light Roy up like a rented pinball machine, he would never have ended up with the Avs. They wouldnt be half the team they are without him between the pipes, and I would be his biggest fan myself if he played for my team..although the Dominator looks pretty damn good right now.<br>
<br>
I will give YOU props though Jing...even though I dont agree with ya about the Avs having class(I acknowledge their talent), you have the kahunas to stand up and speak on behalf of your team. I am sure you will have plenty to cheer for in the next few yrs when Det has retired a number of the superstars on our team. There wont be many teams out there that can run with the Avs then.<br>
<br>
I am finished with this thread...it was nice to vent some emotion over my bitterness. Although Draper isnt my fav player on the Wings(Stevie Y is), I think he is THE best player whose contract was bought for a whole dollar.<br>
<br>
<br>
Hooty<br>
<br>
BTW<br>
I know a couple of Wings players in the last 10 yrs havent been the cleanest of players. Chelios was hated by all Wings fans till he came here... cause he does play dirty. But damn he roxors when he is playing for ya. Vladdy also was known for some crazy antics. But he could also deliver VERY solid CLEAN hits as well. I think it was Brindamour from the Flyers in the cup finals a few yrs ago that he put out of the series with a solid clean hit at center ice. Every time he was on the ice, the other team always had their head up. When he was grped with the rest of the Russian 5, they could move the puck better than most any unit  known in the last 10 yrs. It was very saddening when that accident happened. It was also a big loss..at the time he was a better defenseman than Lidstrom IMO.<br>
<br>
The craziest Wing I can remember in my 13 yrs of following  Wings Hockey was Bob Probert(coke head himself). No  self control whatsoever . The Probert-Domi fight will go down as one of the best of all time. His time as Heavy Weight Champ of the NHL was something else. It was Bowman who wanted him gone I think...and we have been a much better team since we went to finese solid hockey and no goon-only players.<br>
<br>
